servings: 2
time required: 30 minutes
---

olive oil
1 portion cauliflower
1 carrot
1 parsnip
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend
1 tbs balsamic vinegar
½ tbs water
1 tsp brown sugar
1 packet ciabatta
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese
1 packet flaked almonds
1 bag salad leaves
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet Dill & Parsley Mayonnaise
1 onion

Preheat the oven to 220ºC/200ºC fan-forced. Cut
the cauliflower into small florets. Cut the carrot
and parsnip into bite-sized chunks. Place the
veggies on a lined oven tray. Add the Aussie spice
blend and a drizzle of olive oil. Season with salt
and toss to coat. Roast until tender and browned
around the edges, 20-25 minutes. Set aside to cool
slightly.

While the veggies are roasting, thinly slice the red
onion. Heat a large frying pan over a medium-high
heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook the onion,
stirring, until softened, 5-6 minutes. Reduce the
heat to medium, then add the balsamic vinegar,
water and brown sugar and mix well. Cook until
dark and sticky, 3-5 minutes. Transfer to a bowl.

While the onion is cooking, cut or tear the ciabatta
into bite-sized chunks. Place on a second lined
oven tray, then add the garlic & herb seasoning
and a generous drizzle of olive oil. Toss to coat.
Sprinkle with the grated Parmesan cheese. Bake
until golden, 5-8 minutes.

TIP: Adding enough olive oil ensures your croutons
become crunchy and golden.

While the croutons are baking, wipe out the frying
pan and return to a medium-high heat. Toast the
flaked almonds, tossing, until golden
2-3 minutes. Set aside.

Add the spinach & rocket mix, caramelised onion
and a drizzle of white wine vinegar to the roasted
veggies. Toss to combine.

Divide the spiced cauliflower toss between plates.
Top with the herby croutons and dill & parsley
mayonnaise. Garnish with the toasted almonds to
serve.